
\begin{frame}[fragile]
\frametitle{Advective flux}

If $\rho(x,t)$ is the {\blue density} (mass per unit length),
\[
\int_{x_1}^{x_2} \rho(x,t)\, dx = \text{total mass in ~}[x_1,x_2]
\]
and $u(x,t)$ is the velocity, then the {\blue advective flux} is
\[
\rho(x,t)u(x,t)
\]
Units: mass/length $\times$ length/time $=$ mass/time.
\visible<2->{
\vvsp
{\blue Continuity equation (conservation of mass):}
\[
\rho_t + (\rho u)_x = 0
\]
}

\end{frame}
